DEFINITION OF SYSTEM INTERFACES

For the application layer, the common message format of the packet content as shown in the following message format.  Each message must contain a message code, source system number, destination system number, and message transaction ID.  The location ID, terminal ID, and staff ID are mostly used for messages sent from AA to ACP.  The optional message content is variable.

            Status Enquiry for BCS Transactions

Interface Description

When there is no reply after a timed out period, this message is sent from BCSAA to ACP system to enquiry for the status of a transaction.

 

Interface Format

Request (BCS->ACP)

·         Message code = 2073

Reply (ACP->BCS)

·         Message code = 2074

·         Data expected in message header: reply code

Byte Position

Data Type

Size(bytes)

Data

53

Unsigned Integer

8

Current process/last processed transaction ID

 

 

Summary of Error Code

 

Possible reply code:

·         Invalid message format

·         Transaction not received

·         Old transaction

 

 

Status Enquiry for ACP Transactions

Interface Description

When there is no reply after a timed out period, this message is sent from ACP system to BCSAA to enquiry for the status of a transaction.

Interface Format

Request (ACP->BCS)

·         Message code = 3019

·         Data expected in message header: transaction ID, logical terminal ID

Reply (BCS->ACP)

·         Message code = 3020

·         Data expected in message header: reply code

 

Summary of Error Code

Possible reply code:

·         Invalid message format

·         Transaction not received

·         Old transaction

 

 

Byte Position

Data Type

Size(bytes)

Data

53

Unsigned Integer

8

Current process/last processed transaction ID

 

 

Implicit Reverse For ACP Transactions

Interface Description

When transaction status request is received and the transaction was successfully process, AA implicitly perform a reverse and a reverse reply message is returned to ACP.

Interface Format

Reverse Reply (BCS->ACP)

·         Message code = 3022

·         Data expected in message header: reply code, logical terminal ID

 

Summary of Error Code

Possible reply code:

·         Success

·         Reverse cannot be done

Remarks: When ACP send CSC Return Card request to BCS-AA, BCS-AA should compare the account balance in cents in the request with that the CSC card deposit fee, if any.  If the net balance is < 0, reject the request.  If the net balance is >= 0, the request is OK, then, de-associate the CSC card with the account, send successful reply to ACP with the amount of the card deposit fee value.
